{"body": "Let me suggest an alternative that doesn't require a global -- using an instance variable inside the rake namespace. (I just saw [Stack Overflow: rake task variable](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/8342963/rake-task-variable) and it gave me an idea!)\r\n\r\n    namespace :test do\r\n      @tasks = %w(test:units test:functionals test:integration)\r\n      # ...   \r\n    end\r\n\r\nNow, user code can easily modify `@tasks`; see https://gist.github.com/bluemont/5131477 for a simple example.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/14694748", "created_at": "2013-03-11T02:13:55Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/9177#issuecomment-14694748", "updated_at": "2013-03-11T02:16:07Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 9177, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluemont/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluemont/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluemont/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluemont", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluemont/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/bluemont", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluemont/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/d1a1f1e2464b843300e0ff2524ce4468?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fdbb2d77bd76fe13757f45c509cc3b27b.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluemont/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluemont/received_events", "gravatar_id": "d1a1f1e2464b843300e0ff2524ce4468", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluemont/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "bluemont", "type": "Organization", "id": 1750239, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bluemont/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237ec6abd3543c151009cd4"}, "id": 14694748, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/9177"}
